Android Package 'BtTool.apk' is an Android APK used to configure BT related logs of tool
on MediaTek's platforms.
This Android Package is pre-built by MediaTek internal.

WHAT IT DOES?
=============
The Android Package 'BtTool.apk' used to configure BT related logs
for tester to do different log level related testing.

HOW IT WAS BUILT?
==================
This module can be build command:
'mmm -j vendor/mediatek/proprietary/packages/apps/BtTool'.

HOW TO USE IT?
==============
The Android Package 'BtTool.apk' can be launched by MtkLogger of Setting 'Open Bluetooth log Tool'.
or use ADB command:
"adb shell am start -n com.mediatek.bluetooth.dtt/.MainActivity".

Source
==============
All the source code of this Android Package were written by MediaTek co..
